results.name: Greatest prime factor of the n-th 5-smooth number.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: Reap[Do[p = FactorInteger[n][[-1, 1]]; If[p < 7, Sow[p]], {n, 1, 2000}] ][[2, 1]] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Dec 17 2017 *)
program: (MAGMA) [1] cat [Max(PrimeDivisors(k)): k in [2..1500]| PrimeDivisors(k) subset [2, 3, 5]]; // _Marius A. Burtea_, Feb 07 2020
